Change the position of a string in a vector.

Source: R/strings.R
str_move.Rd

Change the position of a string in a character vector.

str_move_before(x, what, move_before)

str_move_after(x, what, move_after)

Arguments

x

(character vector)
what

(string)
move_before

(string)
move_after

(sting)

Examples

x <- c("a", "b", "d", "e", "c", "f")
str_move_before(x, what = "c", move_before = "d")
#> [1] "a" "b" "c" "d" "e" "f"

x <- c("f", "c", "e", "d", "b", "a")
str_move_after(x, what = "c", move_after = "d")
#> [1] "f" "e" "d" "c" "b" "a"

x <- c("a", "b", "d", "e", "c", "f")
str_move_before(x, what = "c", move_before = "d")
#> [1] "a" "b" "c" "d" "e" "f"

x <- c("f", "c", "e", "d", "b", "a")
str_move_after(x, what = "c", move_after = "d")
#> [1] "f" "e" "d" "c" "b" "a"
